This function has this fib(n) so that â€œnâ€ is what that has to be satisfied â€¦ by now you would have got the grip of the step 1 of recursion
the next step is to lay out your logic and write the rest of the function
def fib(n):
    if n &lt;= 1:
        return 0
    else:
        return fib(n-1) + fib(n-2)  # --&gt; go back 2 steps and sum then up
